---
import Badge from "../ui/Badge.astro";
---

<div class="rounded-lg border border-primary/40 bg-card p-6 shadow-soft sm:p-8">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
    <Badge status="vision" />
    <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold">The Stocklore assistant</h3>
  </div>
  <p class="mt-3 max-w-2xl text-sm text-muted-foreground">
    Where this is going: describe the work in plain language, review exactly what the assistant prepared, and approve it. Human-in-the-loop by design — it
    drafts, you decide.
  </p>

  <!-- Illustrative mock conversation — not a live feature -->
  <div class="mt-6 max-w-xl space-y-3" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="ml-auto w-fit max-w-[90%] rounded-lg rounded-br-sm bg-primary-strong px-4 py-2.5 text-sm text-primary-foreground">
      Create a draft invoice for Andrea's Flowers — four Flower Kits, SKU 1234 — and email her the PDF.
    </div>
    <div class="w-fit max-w-[90%] rounded-lg rounded-bl-sm border border-border bg-background px-4 py-2.5 text-sm">
      <p class="font-medium">Draft ready — nothing sent yet:</p>
      <p class="mt-1.5 text-muted-foreground">
        Invoice INV-0108 · Andrea's Flowers · 4 × Flower Kit — $196.00 + HST. Stock is available. Approve to save the draft and email the PDF to andrea@…?
      </p>
      <div class="mt-3 flex gap-2">
        <span class="rounded-md bg-primary-strong px-3.5 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium text-primary-foreground">Approve</span>
        <span class="rounded-md border border-input px-3.5 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium">Edit first</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="mt-5 text-xs text-muted-foreground">
    In development, shipping in phases — answers about your data first, then drafted actions with your sign-off. It acts with <em>your</em> role and permissions,
    and never executes anything on its own.
  </p>
</div>
